node.text:
Went to college? That sucks  if:

You’re not getting what you worked for.

That means the income, the happiness, the fulfillment…

Whatever was your reason for any education- you deserve to get it.

Now, if you didn’t get it, I’, 90% sure it’s not even your fault.

You see we mostly learn a LOT in school but almost never how to use the knowledge we got.

The #1 reason for studying is to pass tests, not to pass life.

Education should give you an edge, not waste your time.

So if you haven’t achieved your goals yet, ask yourself.

“How can I use this education to fulfill my dreams?”

And if you literally can’t accomplish your goals with what you know…

Learn more, train more, gain skills, educate yourself- whatever it takes.

I never was in College because I was too busy being a war refuge, getting kidnapped and watching my livelihood burn down.

And I was still able to retire my parents and become a debt-free man- because I got knowledge that was useful and I used the knowledge until my life changed.

You can do this, too:

Follow 👉@bjkuniversity
Follow 👉@bjkuniversity
Follow 👉@bjkuniversity

And then use what they teach you- learn, and implement is how you get ahead in life!

node.text:
I admit it.

I’m lazy. I HATE working on anything but my dreams.

So I love my team for taking the things I hate off my plate…

But not everyone can afford to have a full team right way.

And that’s where so many entrepreneurs struggle.

They have to do everything:

Customer service, lead generation, accounting, track sales, fulfillment of orders,

Ordering new stuff, test it,...

It’s a nightmare for many but worth it in the end right?

The thing is- you don’t have to do this anymore…

If you sell on Amazon.

Amazon takes care of:
- Tracking
Marketing
Customer service
Shipping Fulfillment
Billing
Getting sales
Statistics
And so much more…

The only thing you need to do is send them the products you wanna sell and literally everything else they do for you.

This empowers you to run a business that would need at least 5-10 people on your own- with almost zero stress.

Amazon takes a cut, but with a profit calculator and the right product, you don’t even notice it.

If you’re profitable in the end, and it’s good enough money to finance your life, who cares how much they get?

It’s a partnership and they help you skip the things that make most entrepreneurs fail.

I don’t know any business that makes business success this easy.

That’s why I love it and why I teach it because everyone deserves a chance at this while it’s still possible don’t you think?

If you wanna get into Amazon FBA and start your stress-free, profitable business:

Follow 👉@bjkuniversity
Follow 👉@bjkuniversity
Follow 👉@bjkuniversity

Watch the training and if you’re eligible, my team will help you get into the program so you can start your business ASAP.

Credit richardgarciaofficial

Stop thinking that.

node.text:
Even after losing everything, I felt a strange…

Almost calming certainty, that I’ll be rich one day.

I don’t know if it was the shock of standing in front of burned ruins…

Or just some weird inner knowledge…

But I knew this is just part of the process.

It’s all gonna be alright in the end.

I want you to have this belief in yourself, too.

Because if you do, you can’t lose:

The best case is you subconsciously start making your belief come true…

And worst case you feel great for believing in yourself every day.

Keep only one thing in mind:

Belief without action is useless. You can’t magically believe rent on your bank account.

But you can believe you’ll find a way to earn it.

Belief needs an outlet and for me, it was my business. 

Maybe for you, it’s gonna be the same?

Follow 👉@bjkuniversity
Follow 👉@bjkuniversity
Follow 👉@bjkuniversity

And check out how an Amazon FBA business works- who knows it might change life, too!

node.text:
What’s your first thought when you wake up?

“Fuck is it that late already?”

“ 5 more minutes….”

“I don’t wanna get up…”

Or do you think…

“Hell yeah, I can’t wait to get up!”

“Hello world, here we go!”( okay no one says that lol)
Here’s why I ask: The thoughts you have in the morning show your outlook in life.

If you’re doing what you love, getting out of bed isn’t hard.

But if you’re not doing what you're truly passionate about, then why get up?

Why bother?

When I wake up, I love to first acknowledge my successes over night, seeing my sales coming ini…

But not because I wanna see the cash come in…

Every sale I make is a sign that my hard work paid off.

My research was on point and my listing works.

The years of studying how Amazon works paid off…

I wake up to see that I made a lot of people’s lives better by what I’m selling because I know I’m giving them the best possible quality.

And, most of all: Every sale reminds me that I truly have changed.

I’m not the loser that lost his restaurant to ignorance anymore…

I’m not the disappointment of the family anymore.

I wake up as the Bashar I always wanted to be.

The sales I make aren't making me who I am.

They are a symptom of who I became.

So find something that fulfills you, something you can’t wait to wake up to.

In my case it’s my Amazon business and @bjkuniversity.

For you it might be something different, or maybe it’s exactly what you need.

In any case, I hope you find it sooner than I did.

MAybe you wanna

Follow 👉 @bjkuniversity
Follow 👉 @bjkuniversity
Follow 👉 @bjkuniversity

And check out what they teach, who know this business model might give you the ticket to the life you always wanted?

node.text:
I made the worst mistake a business owner can make...In the dumbest way possible:

Get some popcorn because this will be dramatic.

Now, you might know I got kidnapped twice while growing up in a warzone and that drained my father of any money he had.

After coming to the US he built a business again and gave me 200k so I can start one, too.

He had a restaurant so I wanted one, too, but I committed the #1 sin no entrepreneur should commit:

I was ignorant & arrogant. I thought I knew exactly how to do this, I need no help.

But guess why I was so arrogant:

I was watching John Taffer’s “Bar Rescue” for 6 months and thought I had a PhD in running bars now.

I mean how dumb can you be? This is reality TV, not real life. They show you what gets views and clicks, not how it really works.

And of course, I fucked up the restaurant so bad I couldn’t even pay insurance before it burned down.

The lesson: Don’t think shows, Youtube videos, and social media content can replace proper training and education. It’s just not true.

If you want to start an Amazon business without being a dumbass like I was, then

Follow 👉@bjkuniversity
Follow 👉@bjkuniversity 
Follow 👉@bjkuniversity 

And learn how Amazon really works!
